<!-- ═══════ DECOMPOSITION ═══════ -->

<div class="asset" style="margin-top:4rem; border-top:1px solid #333; padding-top:3rem;">
  <h2>The Decomposition</h2>
  <p>Alex Rampell at a16z wrote an investment memo about Fly Homes that broke a real estate transaction into its component services. I read that and thought: he's describing what I already built. But I took it further — decompose the agent into special teams, then decompose the special teams into atomic tasks, then route those tasks through a ticketing architecture where every unit of work is a replaceable, measurable primitive.</p>
  <p>This mirrors Amazon's internal architecture. Bezos mandated that every team expose its functionality as a service. I did the same thing with the sales process. The result: any piece can be replaced, measured, or scaled independently. A human can be swapped for an AI. An AI can be swapped for a better AI. The interface stays the same.</p>

