      <h2 style="font-size:1rem; margin-top:0; color:#999;">Adversarial Testing</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:#888;">Red team agents that attack production systems. Every conversation agent has an adversary trying to break it — prompt injection, edge cases, compliance violations. Bugs found by machines before customers hit them.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 style="font-size:1rem; margin-top:0; color:#999;">CI/CD for AI Agents</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:#888;">Cloud Build → Docker → GKE with rollback. Not just code deployment — conversation quality regression tests, guardrail validation, shadow mode for new agent versions running alongside production.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 style="font-size:1rem; margin-top:0; color:#999;">Retro → Macro → Meta Loops</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:#888;">Three feedback layers. Retro: what happened in this conversation. Macro: patterns across thousands of conversations this week. Meta: is the system that generates the system improving. Most teams never get past retro.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 style="font-size:1rem; margin-top:0; color:#999;">The Overnight Machine</h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem; color:#888;">Systems that run while I sleep. Nightly inventory refresh, lead scoring recalculation, stale data detection, automated outreach cadences. Wake up to a dashboard, not a backlog.</p>
